It's time to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house, where nothing has been done except for a bit of decorating.
The hideous electric fireplace and the fireplace floor must go. We need to rebuild the fireplace, replace and smooth out the crumbling plaster. Then build a custom closet.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch…
The dirty part of the job is done.
We found a few dead birds in the chimney, very dry :(
All set for the plasterer next week
The small side niche turned out well
Here comes a new closet in (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look, what we found behind the heating unit!
And we even thought of installing this nice little vent cover, so the chimney doesn't get wet
The chimney sweep has installed the covering and cap. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest up there 🪺
The plasterer is finished. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlayment is in place, I've built a cardboard roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Parts for the floor are ready and can be laid. We're currently taking a tea break
Buhu. Today it's going slowly due to super complicated cuts around the doorposts, so we can have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be newly laid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
We're finally done, but at the end! The crown jewel was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
We still need the floor in the hallway and all the baseboards. The decorator comes in a month, so we have rough plaster finishes for now.
Some more DIY work in the evening to cut or sand the lower sections around the doorposts, where the floor will then fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlayment is now also in the hallway.
We finished the floor in the hallway yesterday! Then up at 5 am to pick up item 1 in Heathrow, a quick nap, and a final push in the hallway, the boards are in place. The gaps will be filled when the adhesive is dry.
